cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with the spread of ideas across a social network. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) because it investigates social influence and behavior-adoption cascades on networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it introduces a new model of complex contagion on networks. It could also be classified under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) because the study of contagion models can have implications for understanding the spread of malware and other cyber threats. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) because it involves the modeling of agents at different stages and their interactions with each other.
